The paper focuses on motion planning, which is a core problem in robotics and control systems. The use of trajectory optimization and sparse roadmap frameworks are common techniques in this field. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the integration of different motion planning algorithms, which involves decision-making and optimization, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for control policy information, which could relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper includes experiments with common application scenarios, which could involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
